Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the Kennedy Space Center in Florida, where he outlined President Donald Trump's vision for American leadership in space. He emphasized the importance of American leadership in space exploration and announced the relaunch of the National Space Council, which will guide a new era of space leadership. Pence also highlighted the role of the commercial space industry and the need for collaboration between government agencies and innovative industries. He expressed confidence that under President Trump's leadership, the United States will return to the moon, go to Mars, and continue to explore space. Pence concluded his speech by calling on the American people to have faith in the future of space exploration and to reach for the stars.